title: Menu for the Ball given by James Hazen Hyde, January 31, 1905
medium: Etching, printed in red ink, on tan laid paper
description: An elaborate menu for a banquet listing the dishes to be served inside an escutcheon bordered by a masked deity of plenty above, fruits of the hunt and of the harvest below, and snaking grapevine on the trellises at either side.
name: Print
